-- Indian shares mark lowest close in 1-1/2 weeks amid risk aversion
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Mon Jun 16, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 16 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell for a second straight session on Monday to their lowest close in 1-1/2 weeks on risk aversion among investors due to tensions in Iraq and Ukraine, with domestic-oriented stocks such as Larsen & Toubro Ltd <LART.NS> taking a hit. [MKTS/GLOB]

Larsen & Toubro provisionally fell 2.3 percent, while Housing Development Finance Corp <HDFC.NS> ended lower 2 percent.